  "prompt": "If he's over me then why does he send me random messages and pictures?",
  "response": "It sounds like you're trying to understand his intentions, which can definitely be confusing. Here are a few possibilities to consider:\n\n1. **He\u2019s Not Fully Over You**: Even if he says he\u2019s moved on, his actions might suggest he still has feelings or unresolved emotions. Sending random messages and pictures could be his way of staying connected or testing the waters.\n\n2. **He\u2019s Seeking Attention or Validation**: Sometimes people reach out because they want to feel wanted or reassured. He might be looking for a reaction from you to boost his ego.\n\n3. **He Misses the Connection**: Even if he\u2019s not romantically interested anymore, he might miss the friendship or the bond you shared and is trying to maintain some level of communication.\n\n4. **He\u2019s Confused or Indecisive**: He might not be sure what he wants, and his messages could reflect that uncertainty. He could be torn between moving on and holding onto the past.\n\n5. **He\u2019s Just Being Friendly**: Sometimes people send messages without any deeper meaning. He might just be checking in or sharing things casually, without intending to stir up emotions.\n\nIf his behavior is confusing or upsetting you, it\u2019s okay to set boundaries or ask him directly what his intentions are. Clear communication can help you both understand where you stand and avoid mixed signals.",
